'''John Harold Douglas''' (29 April 1912 – 1982) was an [[Irish people|Irish]] politician and an [[Independent politician|independent]] member of [[Seanad Éireann]].<ref name="whoswhos1968"/>  He was [[Nominated members of Seanad Éireann|nominated by the Taoiseach]] to the [[8th Seanad]] on 1 October 1954, replacing his deceased father [[James G. Douglas]].<ref name="omdb">{{cite web|url=http://www.oireachtas.ie/members-hist/default.asp?MemberID=2149|title=Mr. John Harold Douglas|work=Members Database 1919 - 2011|publisher=Houses of the Oireachtas|accessdate=4 April 2011}}</ref><ref name="s541124">{{cite web|url=http://debates.oireachtas.ie/seanad/1954/11/24/00007.asp|title=Senator Introduced.|date=24 November 1954|work=Seanad Éireann debates|pages=Vol.44 No.3 p.7|accessdate=4 April 2011}}</ref>

Douglas was a [[Religious Society of Friends|Quaker]] like his father, and succeeded him as [[managing director]] of the family [[Irish linen|linen]] and clothing companies.<ref name="whoswhos1968"/><ref name="DouglasGaughan1998">{{cite book|last1=Douglas|first1=James Green|last2=Gaughan|first2=J. Anthony|title=Memoirs of Senator James G. Douglas (1887-1954), concerned citizen|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LZ5nAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=6 April 2011|year=1998|publisher=University College Dublin Press|isbn=978-1-900621-19-9|page=45}}</ref> On 2 September 1941, he married Hazel ''née'' Malcolm (1915/6–8 September 2009<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rip.ie/death_notices_detail.asp?NoticeID=83974|title=The death has occurred of Hazel Douglas, (née Malcolm) of Dublin|date=11 September 2009|publisher=RIP.ie|accessdate=6 April 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111005033047/http://www.rip.ie/death_notices_detail.asp?NoticeID=83974|archivedate=5 October 2011|df=}}</ref>); they had three children: Jarmila Gay, Averti Karen, and James Malcolm.<ref name="whoswhos1968">{{cite book|title=World who's who in commerce and industry|date=1968-01-01|publisher=Marquis-Who's Who.|page=375}}</ref>

