[[File:Yun Chi-chang.jpg|thumb|200px|Yun Chi-chang (1949)]]
'''Yun Chi-chang'''(윤치창;尹致昌, 1899&ndash;1973) was a [[South Korea]]n diplomat, politician and businessman. Nicknamed '''Namgye''' (남계;南桂), he was the brother of [[Yun Chi-wang]] and half-brother of [[Yun Chi-ho]]. 

He was the Republic of Korea's Ambassador to the [[United Kingdom]] (1948–1951) and Ambassador extraordinary to the Middle East (1960–1961) and Ambassador to [[Turkey]] (1961–1962).

